      • getDocumentResendTemplate

        public java.lang.String getDocumentResendTemplate()
        documentResendTemplate represents how many times and with how big timeouts document will be resent. For example 5,10,15 means that after first failed try application will wait 5 seconds and try again. If second attempt fails, then there will be 10 seconds timeout before third attempt and so on. by default 30,120,1200.
        Returns:
        the documentResendTemplate

      • setDocumentResendTemplate

        public void setDocumentResendTemplate(java.lang.String documentResendTemplate)
        documentResendTemplate represents how many times and with how big timeouts document will be resent. For example 5,10,15 means that after first failed try application will wait 5 seconds and try again. If second attempt fails, then there will be 10 seconds timeout before third attempt and so on. by default 30,120,1200.
        Parameters:
        documentResendTemplate - the documentResendTemplate to set
